Allow a fourth episode

Apogee shipped three, so glue.h refuses to compile for any other number. The
episodes are already parameterised -- each is a header of level names, screen
names and feature flags -- so a fourth needs nothing beyond the door being
opened.

Like patch 0007 this is not a bug fix. It adds a capability the original had no
reason to have. The header it reaches for is not in the submodule: it is
generated by tools/make-episode.py alongside the episode's data files, and
copied in beside upstream's three at configure time.

diff --git a/glue.h b/glue.h
index 7ddfd78..23049d5 100644
--- a/glue.h
+++ b/glue.h
@@ -75,8 +75,10 @@ typedef void interrupt (*InterruptFunction)(void);
 #   include "episode2.h"
 #elif EPISODE == 3
 #   include "episode3.h"
+#elif EPISODE == 4
+#   include "episode4.h"
 #else
-#   error "EPISODE must be defined to 1, 2, or 3"
+#   error "EPISODE must be defined to 1, 2, 3, or 4"
 #endif  /* EPISODE == ... */
 
 /*****************************************************************************
